Pps. &quot;May I&quot; is a more &quot;proper&quot; way of saying &quot;can I&quot;. The reason you feel it is more polite is the fact it is proper english rather than improper grammer. Either way, if someone feels &quot;can I get a sow&quot; would require a please to be responded to, then &quot;may I have a sow&quot; would also require a please. I personally don't feel either statement would require a &quot;please&quot; to be responded too. This is an informal virtual world we are talking about. There are people who spam zones with profanity and exhibit all forms of rude behavior. In my opinion, someone who REQUIRES a please before they help someone in this setting is someone who is looking to get their ego stroked rather then someone worried about politeness. What is more impolite, not saying please, or refusing to help someone because they didn't say please?<br>
<br>
