<br>
I have been a druid almost since this game was started.  I am not sure if this problem of *begging* and *whinning* is as rampant on other servers as it is on Mith Marr - but on Mith Marr it is pretty horrible.<br>
<br>
I *HATE* newbie zones - or any large gathering zones for that matter - like West Commons or Greater Fay.  Why do I hate those zones? Simple... here is a sample of what happened to me in GFay a couple months ago:<br>
<br>
You have entered Greater Faydark<br>
Newbie1 tells you, &quot;can you GG me to NK?&quot;<br>
You beging casting a spell.<br>
You feel the spirit of the wolf enter you.<br>
Newbie2 tells you, &quot;Can you buff me please?&quot;<br>
You tell newbie1, &quot;Sorry hun, I just got here!&quot;<br>
Newbie3 tells you, &quot;Can you bind me at the ork lift - PLEASE!!&quot;<br>
You tell newbie2, &quot;Sorry hun, I can't right now&quot;<br>
Newbie4 waves at you.<br>
newbie4 says, &quot;Can I have SOW?&quot;<br>
You begin casting a spell<br>
Newbie5 tells you, &quot;Do you have anything to spare for a yound druid friend?&quot;<br>
Newbie3 tells you, &quot;Are you there?&quot;<br>
Newbie6 tells you, &quot;Hi there.&quot;<br>
<br>
I mean, seriously, WTF??? When this game first started I remember how reluctant people would be to ask for stuff.  Now they see a high level player and they automatically assume it is your responsibility - no - your duty - to do something for them.  Where did this pathetic lazyness come from??  The worst part - is that they don't even wait for you to zone - the tells start hitting you immediately =(<br>
<br>
I had another one the other day:<br>
<br>
Player1 tells you, &quot;Can you GG me?&quot;<br>
You tell Player1, &quot;Sorry, I can't right now.&quot;<br>
Player1 tells you, &quot;Why not?&quot;<br>
<br>
Why not? Why not? When the hell did it become anyone else's business my reasons for not taking someone's lazy ass accross the continent? The other ones that piss me off are the ones that send you a tell with a plain old &quot;Hello&quot; - you look at the name, it's no one you know - you know they are getting ready to beg - why not save you the typing and just ask for what they want outright? Lately, when I get those &quot;Hello!&quot; tells, they just ignored...<br>
<br>
Lately, I have used an AFK message to try to minimize the number of responses I have to send out, here is what happened about 2 weeks ago:<br>
<br>
Dude1 tells you, &quot;Can you GG me?&quot;<br>
You tell Dude1, &quot;Sorry, I am AFK right now - I am not currently gating, buffing, giving anything away, powerleveling, binding - Sorry!&quot;<br>
Dude1 tells you, &quot;So - can you GG Me?&quot;<br>
<br>
Grrrr! So now people can't read either =( I seriously don't mind helping people if I have nothing to do.  I never charge for gates, regardless of player level, an I don't mind un-memming my spells to buff some newbie.  However, I am NOT going to drop what I am doing to do these things.  Someone said earlier in this thread that as a druid it is my &quot;responsibility?&quot; - Uhm...all I can say is what a crock! We play this game for fun - NOTHING in this game is my responsibility.  Hell, a newbie could be standing in front of me, about to die, and me - having full mana - could heal him.  Do I generally do that? Yes.  Do I do it because it's my responsibility? No.  I do it cause I am not a b****! (most of the time, hehe)<br>
<br>
I am just so fed up with people that think that we owe them something.  I have several lower level characters that I play - rogue, Bard, SK, Enchanter, Necro.  I always take the boat - why? Because I know what a royal pain in the ass it is to get bugged every 5 minutes with people asking/whining about something.  If there is a druid trying to make some money and announces that he/she is gating, then I will pay for my gate - no biggie - but I don't go around begging - that's just sad...<br>
<br>
I worked hard for my level - for my cash.  Hell I wore leather armor until level 28 or so - and still I survived! I didn't die a horrible death or stopped playing the game because I didn't get uber buffs or uber gear.  People just need to quit their begging and whining, STFU and get what they want themselves.  <br>
<br>
And if you harrass me for a gate, here is what you will get:<br>
<br>
&quot;You want a ride? Take the dammed boat, k thx!&quot;<br>
