Ok now, on topic. <br>
<br>
Opening up, I agree with the poster previous to BobJiz, I too was raised in the school of hard knocks, but I think I had it a little tad bit harder! =P I was raised with a Warrior in the banded hunt, the blacksmithing era, where my warrior was in leather until level 20 (warrior newb crap is Ringmail, I had LEATHER) ok, I remember trying to run to a guild meeting and I was late, so I used my Druid as well (I played them both) I found out Druids get group gate in the future and I was gonna make sure no one had this problem again.<br>
<br>
Now in my opinion Druids are the most diverse class in Norrath, we have the ability to play any role as well as provide some of the Wisdom fortunate classes some &quot;services&quot; notice it's quoted, which means we aren't obligated to do it, because it's a service.<br>
<br>
As far as the SoW issue, and how to ask.<br>
In some ways, I agree with &quot;Maxipus&quot; lol, but just because please isn't said, doesn't mean that they don't have to get SoWed.....NOTE: That comment alone is TRUE on it's own, minus any factions (bad day, etc etc)<br>
<br>
NOTE: Please or roleplaying is not considered kissing ass, it's considered being polite, and you find out that a couple of simple words can help you out. I play alts, sometimes I get a little lazy yes, I'll ask for a gate somewhere, if I don't get it, tough sh*t, I'll run, but when I ask, since I know it's a favor and how I would react being a Druid as well<br>
<br>
Alt tells Druid: Hey, what's up, this is Asaph, was just wondering if you have time for a gate, if ya busy, it's coo!<br>
<br>
I'm speaking on the Druid's level, I'm not begging, and if he says no...tough sh*t, I'll run.<br>
<br>
I am commonly nice, I sometimes go outta my way for people I don't know, I've built a good rep on my server doing things like that. but on the occasion, don't beat around the bush whenever someone asks you something, that's how confrontations get started, another ex.<br>
<br>
SoW's are naturally manaless, above level 50, casting SoW, you barely see any bar movement, if you have it memmed, so be it, cast it, be nice, cancel your gate for 2 secs, make some people happy, unless they act otherwise. I know whenever I see someone I don't know, run up to me, and wave, that's usually a symbol that they want SoW, it's been a habit to where i'll just stand up and cast it, and they have SoW before their finished typing &quot;Can I get a SoW&quot; all I get is the thanks, they run off, so be it, I'm still playing the game, he still plays the game....in RL, you still eat, sleep and sh*t, move on, act as if you have a life, don't make a big deal out of this.<br>
<br>
