I did a Naggy raid yesterday.  I alone picked up about 1/2 the raid from all over the EQ world, from Iceclad to Tox to Dread and brought them to Lava for Naggy.  Along the way, I got 11 non-raid tells from other players sitting at druid rings looking for ports.  I ported each and every one of them where they needed to go, including one guy (Wonk) and his buddy (Pdiddy), after buffing them to hell so they wouldn't die (Wonk fell and died the first time I ported him).<br>
<br>
After I was done, 9 out of the 11 people that I ported wanted to donate to me for being so nice to them.  I simply told them: Pay it Forward.<br>
<br>
Now, if you've ever seen that movie, you know what I mean.  Pay it forward means don't pay me back for what I did for you, but do something for some other people.  There are so many assholes in EQ (ex: Stungun or whatever your name is) that telling someone to Pay it Forward might just make everyone's EQ experience a little bit better.  I imagine that 5 out of those 9 just might do something nice for someone else because I made their day for them.  They might flip a few coins to a beginner, or heal a guy who needs it, or SoW someone while they are waiting for their friends to show up at the gate to North Freeport.<br>
<br>
Whatever the case, I just hope I made a few people happy out there, and maybe they will continue the trend.  <br>
